  "source_id": "heart-failure-hf-differentiation-between-preserved-and-reduced-ejection-fraction",
  "name": "Heart Failure with Ejection Fraction Differentiation",
  "description": "This test case evaluates the ability to identify patients with heart failure and differentiate between preserved (HFpEF, EF\u226550%) and reduced ejection fraction (HFrEF, EF<50%). The eMERGE algorithm uses ICD-9 codes (428.X), NLP-detected mentions in clinical notes, and echocardiography ejection fraction measurements. Cases are classified as definite, probable, or possible based on corroborating evidence within specified time windows.",
  "prompt": "Find all adult patients diagnosed with heart failure, including those with preserved ejection fraction (greater than 50%) and those with reduced ejection fraction (less than 50%), along with their echocardiogram ejection fraction measurements.",
